				<li id="16630896" class="cmnt-root" data="9" data-d="1650341014000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579576/Death-Lightning" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">19 Apr 2022 00:03</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16630896" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">It&apos;s not terrible, but it could be tweaked a bit to be more viable. The damage is respectable, the FP cost acceptable, the range is okay, the recovery fair, and, for what it does, the cast time is decent, but, like a lot of lightning spells, it really just has to hit targets in its purview. There&apos;s just no excuse for a boss spell that needs 2 slots with a decent wind-up to completely miss the enemy YOU&apos;RE LOCKED ONTO, let alone any others in range. Other fixes it needs would be to have the charged version have a larger range (as of right now, it just gives a very slight increase in damage and more bolts to strike enemies with, although doesn&apos;t actually guarantee all enemies in range will be hit which, again, is ridiculous) and to make it chainable (preferably, at half the initial cast time). The death blight build-up could be better, certainly, but the clouds are still handy for masking your next move and look cool; if the spell was chainable, it would make the clouds much more useful since it makes it difficult to gauge whether it&apos;s now safe to attack you or they&apos;re attacking into the follow-up strike. To be PvP viable, nova spells need to be able to trade well against aggression, and prevent follow-up attacks. Think Wrath of Gold, which is literally the gold standard for nova-type spells right now.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16630896" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16630896" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>10</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>1</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16630896"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16630896" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16630896"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
