				<li id="16440564" class="cmnt-root" data="40" data-d="1646301471000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579576/Death-Lightning" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">03 Mar 2022 04:57</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16440564" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">This Isn&apos;t a Sorcery. It&apos;s a Incantation. It&apos;s obtained via the Remembrance of Fortissax. Which In itself is a Optional Boss fight beneath the Erdtree. Who is also gated behind 2 questlines. <br/><br/>To get there, you need to Unlock Nokron the Eternal city. From the Ancestral Woods Bonfire, Head North east, Right to the wall, you&apos;ll eventually find a Jellyfish, there&apos;s a ledge, jump down that unlocks a new grace point. <br/><br/>Progress through that area eventually and you&apos;ll find a boss fight. A Duo Gargoyle fight.  After there&apos;s a new bonefire in that arena and a coffin that takes you to the Secret Erdtree underground area.  Eventually in that area, at the top in the water area there&apos;s a grace point, a trio invasion boss fight and then Fia&apos;s quest. <br/>Talk to her, accept her offers and resting at the Gracepoint will eventually unlock a the memory for this boss for you to fight. <br/><br/>As an extra note, it is required to have found one half of the cursemark of death I believe. <br/><br/>Have fun. </p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16440564" class="cmt-reply pull-ri